$interpreted: Alliance Trooper: Scram! Who gave you permission to stand around and chat!?
Smug Beast: Look at them. They can't even follow a simple rule. So, that's why I say the bugs need the East Alliance to educate them.
Chill Beast: Indeed. Look over there. It's hard to imagine how, without us, the bugs would find a way to live.
Insect Man: Th-This is my food stamp for the month.
Tindoiimu: (This is what I get for everything I've endured, for swallowing my pride... nine years... and everything is still the same...)
Juan Yun: The view here is much nicer, am I right?
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: Look, head in the clouds. Didn't even notice that I came in.
Tindoiimu: Lord Juan Yun, is there something that requires you to be here in the middle of the night?
Juan Yun: I... I've come to apologize. For that whole mess earlier today... I should have been paying more attention.
Tindoiimu: ...Don't worry about it. If it weren't for you, I wouldn't have been able to come home in the first place.
Juan Yun: Oh, right—Arbiter Maeok has sent a messenger to inform your parents of your return.
Juan Yun: Someone should be here soon to take you back to the imperial palace for a visit.
Tindoiimu: What!? But—
Juan Yun: It's ok—keep it like a secret. Go see them and come back, no one's the wiser.
Tindoiimu: .........
Tindoiimu: ...Thank you. Really.
Juan Yun: .........
Juan Yun: Guess I'm not allow to joke with you too much. Could be dangerous.
Tindoiimu: Huh?
Juan Yun: Well—
Alliance Trooper: Lord Juan Yun, the Insect king has sent a messenger with a letter for the princess. The arbiter has told me to bring him here directly.
Tindoiimu: A letter for me?
Tindoiimu: "Child, your mother and I are so happy that you have returned. This is a magnanimous and merciful gesture from the Alliance.
Tindoiimu: As princess, you must act even more in accordance with the rules, and not forget this gracious act. Think and act carefully..."
Tindoiimu: "...As your mother and I have already retired to our quarters for the night, we are unable to meet with you..."
Tindoiimu: "We hope that after tomorrow's Metamorphosis, you can return swiftly to the Alliance"
Juan Yun: What is this!? They can't get out of bed? You haven't seen your daughter in nine years!!
Tindoiimu: It's an excuse. They just don't want to see me.
Juan Yun: How could that be!?
Tindoiimu: If they see me,
Tindoiimu: they'll be accused of conspiring to bring me home.
Tindoiimu: It'll cause trouble.
Juan Yun: But... didn't they say they're happy you're here?
Tindoiimu: ...They're not. They're reprimanding me for coming back so recklessly. It may cause trouble for our tribe.
Juan Yun: Eh!?
Tindoiimu: To my father and mother, I am a political hostage first, daughter second.
Tindoiimu: This is what being a hostage means, Juan Yun. Hostage even from my parents' love.
Juan Yun: .........
Errand Boy: Well, if you knew that, why'd you come back here?
Errand Boy: First, you steal my mom, now you endanger the whole tribe?
Tindoiimu: Were you eavesdropping? And did you say I stole your...
Tindoiimu: Wait... Faayida!?
Faayida: Who gave you the right to take my mom away!? Does the princess really have that much power...?
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: Child, you misunderstand. The princess did not go on her own accord...
Faayida: It's her fault mom's gone! If it's a misunderstanding, then just bring her back!
Tindoiimu: Wait—
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: ...In your hand... is that... ?
Tindoiimu: My nanny wanted me to give this to him—her son—for his birthday...
Juan Yun: Oh?
Juan Yun: Well then... aren't you going to chase after him?
Tindoiimu: No. He will attend the Metamorphosis. I will give it to him then...
